   <p>&nbsp;</p>

<a name="fun"></a>
<p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px 'Times New Roman'; color: #4e72a2;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Post Fundamentals&nbsp;</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Session One&nbsp;</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Recommended Topic: Designed Alliance and the Wheel of Life</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What is the alliance that you and your mentor coach want to design? You can use this as an opportunity to begin designing an alliance. It&rsquo;s important to note that a Designed Alliance is a process, not an event. In all relationships, including coaching relationships, the design of the alliance is ongoing. Whenever a new relationship begins&mdash;and most particularly whenever there is challenge, confusion or difficulty&mdash;there is an opportunity to design or to continue the design of the alliance.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">As you practice this both with clients and in your life, you&rsquo;ll notice that your relationships will become clearer, more honest and more grounded.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>For the Client</strong><br /> Score your Wheel of Life with your coach. Where are you out of balance in your life? What specific action or actions will you take to raise the score in a particular area? Don&rsquo;t forget to have your mentor coach hold you accountable!</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>For the Coach</strong><br /> The Wheel of Life is a great place to begin coaching with a client. It provides a clear snapshot of a client&rsquo;s life and LOTS of opportunities for coaching.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Recommended homework between calls:</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Pay attention to Designed Alliances in your life and practice designing an alliance at least twice</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Take action to create more balance in at least one area on your Wheel of Life.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Session Two&nbsp;</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Recommended Topic: Practice Clients and Accountability</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">On the Call Part One:</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">De-brief homework from last call:</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What did you learn about Designed Alliance?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What actions did you take around your Wheel of Life?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">On the Call Part Two:&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">We strongly recommend that you find several practice clients to coach while you are taking classes with CTI. If you are clear that you want to become a professional coach, you&rsquo;ll want to begin building your coaching practice as soon as possible.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>For the Client</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">As such, there are so MANY different ways to apply Co-Active&reg; Coaching skills. Regardless of how you plan to use what you are learning, it will be helpful to set up a few coaching clients to practice your skills. You will LEARN so much when you practice and then apply what you learn in your classes. If you really want to get your money&rsquo;s worth from the CTI curriculum, having even a few practice clients is the way to go.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">On this call, talk with your mentor coach about finding practice clients. Who might you invite?&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What would be the best way to set it up?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What is the accountability you would like your mentor coach to hold for you?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>For the Coach</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Remember, Accountability is not about making people do something. Instead, it is about holding what the client SAID they would do, cleanly and without judgment. Accountability supports clear action and assists the client in being grounded about where they are truly committed.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Recommended homework between calls:</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Add at least 2 clients. The structure can be whatever works for you. They can be paying clients or practice clients, whatever will serve you best. (If your client has only taken Fundamentals and has not yet signed up for or taken Fulfillment, recommend that they practice the skills they have learned with at least two people and if they want clients, to have practice clients only.)</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Notice where in your life you need to practice the skill of Accountability. Who in your life do you need to hold accountable and for what?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>



<a name="ful"></a>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px 'Times New Roman'; color: #4e72a2;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Post Fulfillment</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Session Three</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Recommended Topic: Values</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">On the call Part One:&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">De-brief homework from last call.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;How did you do in setting up at least 2 practice clients?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;What did you learn about holding people accountable?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 36.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">On the Call Part Two:&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Work with your coach around the values clarification process that you began in Fulfillment.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What values are you honoring fully?&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What values are being stepped on?&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What would change if you started honoring your values more fully?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 6.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>For the Client</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">With your coach, design at least one action step you can take to begin honoring your values more fully. What is the one action that, if you took it, would change your life completely?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>For the Coach</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">As clients begin to respect and honor their values, they move to a place of deeper authenticity and resonance in their lives. So, the values clarification process is just the beginning of walking a client towards the resonance of Fulfillment.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Recommended homework between calls:</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Take the action steps you designed with your coach to raise the score around one or more of your values</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Practice doing values clarification with your coaching clients</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Session Four&nbsp;</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Recommended Topic: The Voice of the Saboteur</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">On the call Part One:&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Debrief homework from last call.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What actions did you take to honor one or more of your values?&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What was the shift you noticed as a result?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What did you learn by doing values clarification with your coaching clients?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 18.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">On the Call Part Two:&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Use this call to explore the voice of your Saboteur with your mentor coach.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 2.1px; text-indent: -2.1px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What does he or she sound like?&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 2.1px; text-indent: -2.1px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What are the kinds of things he or she says?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 6.0px 2.1px; text-indent: -2.1px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What are the most effective ways for you to move beyond the dissonant voice of the Saboteur?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Recommended homework between calls:</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">For one hour a day, count the number of times your Saboteur speaks up.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 24.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">With your coaching clients, practice listening for the dissonant voice of the Saboteur.</span></p>




<a name="bal"></a>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px 'Times New Roman'; color: #4e72a2;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Post Balance</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Session Five&nbsp;</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Recommended Topic: Saying Yes and Saying No</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">On the call Part One:&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Debrief homework from last call.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What did you learn about your Saboteur from the homework exercise?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 6.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What did you learn by doing Values Clarification with your coaching clients?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 6.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>For the Client</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">In your Balance course, you created a list of 3 &lsquo;Yes&rsquo;s&rsquo; and 3 &lsquo;No&rsquo;s&rsquo;. Share these with your mentor coach to deepen your learning and forward the action.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Recommended homework in between calls:</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 2.1px; text-indent: -2.1px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Any actions that you designed with your mentor coach as a result of this call.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 2.1px; text-indent: -2.1px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Practice working with your coaching clients around saying &lsquo;Yes&rsquo; and saying &lsquo;No&rsquo;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Session Six&nbsp;</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Recommended Topic: Choosing Perspectives</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">On the call Part One:&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Debrief homework from last call.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 2.1px; text-indent: -2.1px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What actions did you take to make your Yes&rsquo;s and No&rsquo;s more real?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 2.1px; text-indent: -2.1px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What did you learn by working with Yes and No with your coaching clients?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 20.1px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">On the call Part Two:&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Work with your mentor coach about a situation in which you feel stuck. Encourage your mentor coach to use the Balance Formula.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What is the topic?&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What are the other perspectives?&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Which one do you choose?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 6.0px 18.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>For the Client</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">In your Balance course, one of the important things you learned was that we have a choice in the perspective through which we view any particular circumstances or set of circumstances. The ability to be fluid and adopt the perspective that is most useful for us is one of life&rsquo;s greatest skills.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 6.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Recommended homework in between calls:</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 2.1px; text-indent: -2.1px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Any actions that you designed with your mentor coach as a result of this call.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 2.1px; text-indent: -2.1px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Whenever you feel stuck or ineffective, practice shifting your perspective. What do you notice?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 24.0px 2.1px; text-indent: -2.1px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Practice using the Balance Coaching Formula&reg; with your coaching clients.</span></p>


<a name="pro"></a>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px 'Times New Roman'; color: #4e72a2;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Post Process</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Session Seven&nbsp;</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Recommended Topic: Being With What Is Hard To Be With</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">On the call Part One:&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Debrief homework from last call.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What actions did you take as a result of your last call with your mentor coach?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What did you notice about choosing a different perspective?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 6.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What did you discover by using the Balance Coaching Formula&reg; with your coaching clients?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>For the Client</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">In your Process course you explored what you can&rsquo;t be with and the Energy Pattern. You also explored how to be with emotions and how to deepen the experience of emotions.&nbsp; As you learn to be with and experience what has been difficult to be with, energy is released and new resources and awareness becomes available for growth and moving forward.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Talk with your mentor coach about what you are learning about the value of being with difficult emotions, what resources become available to you as you experience what is hard to be with, about&nbsp; being &lsquo;on&rsquo; or &lsquo;off&rsquo; purpose in your life. Is the general flow of your life rooted in your life purpose or is your river off-course in some places?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 6.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>For the Coach</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Recommended homework in between calls:</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Review any actions that you designed with your mentor coach as a result of this call.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Practice doing Process coaching with one or more of your coaching clients.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 6.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Session Eight&nbsp;</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>Recommended Topic: Being Present and Completion</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">On the call Part One:&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">De-brief homework from last call.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 2.1px; text-indent: -2.1px; lh: 12.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What actions did you take as a result of your last call with your mentor coach?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 2.1px; text-indent: -2.1px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What opened up for you when you used Process coaching with a client?</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 38.1px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b; min-height: 12.0px;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>For the Client</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Process is about being fully PRESENT with whatever is in your life without moving to fix it or change it or hide it. Talk with your mentor coach about&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Where you are most challenged in being present in your life.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font 13.0px Arial; color: #3f160b;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">What pulls you away?&nbsp; This will be your final call with your mentor coach. What do you need to say to be complete</span><span style="font: 9.0px Arial; letter-spacing: 0.0px;">?</span></p>
</p>


